##How to make Arepas! By Veronica##


#Variables
Ingredient Water #(to measure)
Ingr Corn flour #(1-2 c)
Ingr cheese #(to taste)
Ingr Salt #(only a pinch!)
Ingr Oil
Ingr Chicken #(1/2 a chicken breast)
Ingr Mayonnaise #(5 tbsp)
Ingr Avocado

Tool pan 
Tool bowl
Tool tostiarepa
Tool spatula

Conditions:
Boolean isVegan
Boolean hasTostiArepa


Arepas MakeArepas(water, corn flour, salt) {

Step 1: Combine water + corn flour + salt
Begin:
   1c corn flour, slowly add in water 
   make sure consistency is correct 
   mix = corn flour + water + salt

   if isVegan !==:
   cheeseArepa = mix + cheese
End//

Step 2: Roll mix into balls 
Begin:
   balls = circular motion + mix

   if manyPeople(such as this class):
    balls == 1/2 palm 

   if familyBreakfast:
     balls == 3/4 palm 

   if veryHungry:
     balls = full palm 

End//

Step 3: cook Arepas
Begin:
  If tostiArepa !==:
    pan + oil (usually use Olive Oil)
    cookedArepa = pan + oil + balls + time + 4 flips
    Pro tip: In order to get signature "marks" on arepas, flatten with bottom of spatula
    remove from pan and open! 

  If tostiArepa ==:
    cookedArepa = mix + tostiArepa + time 
End//
}



Filling MakeReinaPepiada(chicken, mayonnaise, avocado) {
	Step 1: Shred chicken 
	Pro tip: buy pre-shredded chicken to save time!

	Step 2: Create "guac"
	pit avocado, smash, add salt and olive oil

	Step 3: Combine
	reinaPepiada = chicken + guac + mayonnaise
}
